                    "description": "Teaching and developing courses in the Bachelor's and Master's Programme Cultural Studies. Conducting research on heritage learning and historical representation in museums. Working on a project that aims to stimulate the exchange of knowledge and expertise on heritage learning between academics, teachers, teacher trainers, and heritage educators.\n\nCourse development\n* 'Examining Cultural Heritage' (coordinator & co-author)\n* 'Perspectives on the Netherlands in the modern era' (co-author & tutor)\n* Professional development courses for history teachers (coordinator & co-author)\n\nTeaching\n* 'Research Workshop: BA Thesis Cultural History'\n* 'Cultural Heritage' (supervision and examination)\n* 'Research and Analysis' (paper supervision)\n* 'Memory Culture of the Air Warfare of WW II', 'Historical Culture: Local History in Museums' (co-led seminars)\n* Supervision of master's theses\n* Lectures at several study days\n\nResearch\n* Project lead of 'Objects in perspective: using questions in museums to start discussion about sensitive topics in the history classroom'\n* Co-authored publications on historical empathy in museums, the use of Holocaust heritage in the primary school context, and developments in city museums\n* Organised expert meetings and study days on heritage learning\n* Presented lectures and papers and facilitated workshops at (inter)national conferences on heritage learning, citizenship education, and narrative strategies in museum exhibitions",
                    "title": "Assistant Professor",
                    "employment_type": null
                }
            ]
